one attacks targeting the United Arab Emirates. NBC News’ Courtney Kube reports.</media:description><media:subTitle type="text/srt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778282143240_nn_cku_iran_tankers_260508.srt"></media:subTitle><media:subTitle type="text/vtt" lang="en-US" url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/nbcnews/captions/2026/05/1778282143240_nn_cku_iran_tankers_260508.vtt"></media:subTitle></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/mpx/2704722219/2026_05/1778282143240_nn_cku_iran_tankers_260508_S3_1920x1080-9912v1.jpg"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 23:15:49 GMT</pubDate><title>U.S. and Iran exchange fire as Trump says ceasefire still holds</title><updateDate>Sat, 09 May 2026 00:23:08 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dc:creator>Courtney Kube</dc:creator><dc:creator>Mosheh Gains</dc:creator><dc:creator>Garrett Haake</dc:creator><dc:creator>Natasha Lebedeva</dc:creator><dc:contributor>Monica Alba</dc:contributor><dc:contributor>Steve Kopack</dc:contributor><dateTimeWritten>Fri, 08 May 2026 21:47:53 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>Saudi officials were angered by President Donald Trump’s surprise announcement that the U.S. would start guiding ships through the Strait of Hormuz, fearing the move could spur more Iranian attacks on Gulf allies.</description><expires>2112-01-01T00:00:00.000+0000</expires><guid>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/national-security/saudis-feared-trumps-project-freedom-spur-iran-attack-officials-say-rcna344124</guid><link>https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/national-security/saudis-feared-trumps-project-freedom-spur-iran-attack-officials-say-rcna344124</link><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-strait-of-hormuz-mn-1455-0bf5ba.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1187" width="1800"><media:credit>Kyodo via AP</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Vessels in Strait of Hormuz</media:text><media:description type="plain">Vessels in the Strait of Hormuz off Bandar Abbas, southern Iran, on May 5, 2026.</media:description></media:content><media:content url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260507-trump-ww-1644-7df527.jpg" type="image/jpeg" medium="image" height="1631" width="2500"><media:credit>Yuri Gripas</media:credit><media:text type="plain">Donald Trump gazes to the side while standing in front of a white wall in the White House.</media:text><media:description type="plain">President Donald Trump in the East Room of the White House on Wednesday.</media:description></media:content><media:thumbnail url="https://media-cldnry.s-nbcnews.com/image/upload/t_fit_1500w/rockcms/2026-05/260508-strait-of-hormuz-mn-1455-0bf5ba.jpg" height="1187" width="1800"></media:thumbnail><pubDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 21:47:53 GMT</pubDate><title>Saudis feared Trump’s Project Freedom would spur Iran to attack, officials say</title><updateDate>Fri, 08 May 2026 21:47:53 GMT</updateDate></item><item><dateTimeWritten>Sat, 09 May 2026 11:46:18 GMT</dateTimeWritten><description>A Frontier Airlines plane had to abort its takeoff after hitting a person on the runway at Denver International Airport. The airline says all 224 passengers and seven crew members evacuated safely from the plane. The airport says the emergency response is ongoing and the runway where the pedestrian was struck will remain closed as the investigation continues. NBC’s Valerie Castro reports for Saturday TODAY. </description><expires>2056-05-09T11:45:04.000+0000</expires><guid isPermaLink="false">tdy_sat_castro_frontier_airlines_260509</guid><link>https://www.today.com/video/frontier-airlines-plane-hits-pedestrian-on-denver-airport-runway-263042629903</link><media:content url="https://prodamdnewsencoding.akamaized.net/NBC_News_Digital/tdy_sat_castro_frontier_airlines_260509/1/abs/index.m3u8" medium="